nneeww__ooppttiioonnaall__iinntteerrvvaall__vvaarr(start: Union[ortools.sat.python.cp_model_helper.LinearExpr, ForwardRef('IntVar'), int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64], size: Union[ortools.sat.python.cp_model_helper.LinearExpr, ForwardRef('IntVar'), int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64], end: Union[ortools.sat.python.cp_model_helper.LinearExpr, ForwardRef('IntVar'), int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64], is_present: Union[ortools.sat.python.cp_model_helper.Literal, int, numpy.int8, numpy.uint8, numpy.int32, numpy.uint32, numpy.int64, numpy.uint64, bool], name: str) -> ortools.sat.python.cp_model.IntervalVar method of ortools.sat.python.cp_model.CpModel instance
    Creates an optional interval var from start, size, end, and is_present.

    An optional interval variable is a constraint, that is itself used in other
    constraints like NoOverlap. This constraint is protected by a presence
    literal that indicates if it is active or not.

    Internally, it ensures that `is_present` implies `start + size ==
    end`.

    Args:
      start: The start of the interval. It must be of the form a * var + b.
      size: The size of the interval. It must be of the form a * var + b.
      end: The end of the interval. It must be of the form a * var + b.
      is_present: A literal that indicates if the interval is active or not. A
        inactive interval is simply ignored by all constraints.
      name: The name of the interval variable.

    Returns:
      An `IntervalVar` object.
